'''''Philiris radicala''''' is a species of [[butterfly]] of the family [[Lycaenidae]]. It is found in [[Western Province (Papua New Guinea)|Western Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]].

The length of the forewings is about 17&nbsp;mm. The ground colour of the forewings is bright shining turquoise, the costa and termen broadly black. The hindwings are bright shining turquoise, the termen broadly black.

==Etymology==
The species name refers to the extraordinary colouration of the male upperside and overall divergent morphology of this species and is derived from ''radicala''.<ref>[https://www.pensoft.net/inc/journals/download.php?fileId=8136&fileTable=J_GALLEYS Six new species of ''Philiris'' Röber, 1891 (Lepidoptera, Lycaenidae) from Papua New Guinea]</ref>

